ATTRIBUTION

This Python implementation is a derivative work based on the original MATLAB
implementation by Etienne Corman and Keenan Crane, available at:
https://github.com/etcorman/RectangularSurfaceParameterization

The core algorithm implements the method described in:

  "Rectangular Surface Parameterization"
  Etienne Corman and Keenan Crane
  ACM Transactions on Graphics (SIGGRAPH), 2025

If you use this software in academic work, please cite the original paper:

  @article{Corman:2025:RSP,
    author = {Corman, Etienne and Crane, Keenan},
    title = {Rectangular Surface Parameterization},
    journal = {ACM Trans. Graph.},
    volume = {44},
    number = {4},
    year = {2025},
    publisher = {ACM},
    address = {New York, NY, USA},
  }

---

PYTHON CONVERSION

This Python implementation was created by Mattias Fagerlund, including:
- Complete port of all MATLAB algorithms to Python/NumPy/SciPy
- Integration with libQEx for quad mesh extraction
- Mesh preprocessing utilities
- Visualization and verification tools

The conversion preserves the mathematical algorithms exactly as designed by
Corman and Crane. All credit for the underlying method belongs to the
original authors.

